ivardefs.name: contains_
ivardefs.desc: The codes that are contained in the value set expansion.

ivardefs.name: identifier
ivardefs.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies this expansion of the valueset, based on a unique combination of the provided parameters, the system default parameters, and the underlying system code system versions etc. Systems may re-use the same identifier as l

ivardefs.name: offset
ivardefs.desc: If paging is being used, the offset at which this resource starts.  I.e. this resource is a partial view into the expansion. If paging is not being used, this element SHALL NOT be present.

ivardefs.name: parameter_
ivardefs.desc: A parameter that controlled the expansion process. These parameters may be used by users of expanded value sets to check whether the expansion is suitable for a particular purpose, or to pick the correct expansion.

ivardefs.name: property_
ivardefs.desc: A property defines an additional slot through which additional information can be provided about a concept.

ivardefs.name: timestamp
ivardefs.desc: The time at which the expansion was produced by the expanding system.

ivardefs.name: total
ivardefs.desc: The total number of concepts in the expansion. If the number of concept nodes in this resource is less than the stated number, then the server can return more using the offset parameter.

properties.desc: A value set can also be "expanded", where the value set is turned into a simple collection of enumerated codes. This element holds the expansion, if it has been performed.
